HEADWORD: Kohl
<hw>Kohl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Alcohol</er>.]</ety> <def>A mixture of soot and other ingredients,
used by Egyptian and other Eastern women to darken the edges of the
eyelids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

